p align=left class=m><span class=title>   Sky rule need to be changed with strong guide line</span><hr size=1> *IMPORTANT*<br>
Don't take this as rant to CA<br>
<br>
CA reserved 24th , 25th , 26th for sky raid.<br>
Each raid would start from 4pm PST.<br>
I reserved 26th 5am PST for 1-4th isle after their reservation.<br>
Of course CA has priority, but i thought they would go over 4+ isle until my date<br>
and would cause no trouble.<br>
<br>
Today(25th) i logged in and noticed CA is on Djorn isle.<br>
I asked them what was their plan, and it was<br>
<br>
24th = clear isle1 and get key and camp<br>
25th = clear isle1 again and move up<br>
26th = moving up<br>
<br>
Sky is the only plane which is reservable for 3 days.<br>
I remember it is for &quot;FULL 1 to 8 isle&quot; raid.<br>
Because it can't be done in 1 day unless ppl have Necro with key already.<br>
<br>
I talked with CA raid leader and he told me this plan was usual for him, every raid he joined did same.<br>
So, probably there are more ppl who would/will do this.<br>
Reserving whole day for only 1 isle is nothing but waste.<br>
Sky is being perma camped plane like Fear Hate,<br>
We need to do something on this not to make dead time.<br>
If we allow ppl to reserve full 3 days without strong reason,<br>
it will be overcrowded especialy weekends.<br>
<br>
***EDITED***<br>
I posted my idea of rule under this sled.<br>
Please read it.<br>
<br>
Roatus<br>
Guild leader of Zenith <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uroatusbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoatusBH</A> at: 5/27/01 12:05:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwayun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wayun</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_whitespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>aka Valeer</span><br>  Posts: 584<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/25/01 11:44:29 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/image/49/2586249.jpg?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sky rule need to be changed with strong guide line</span><hr size=1> But what of the guilds who can't field an average of 55th level?<br>
<br>
What about the guilds who are raiding Sky for the first time? Or under leadership who is not &quot;seasoned&quot; in a plane. They will (no doubt) go slower.<br>
<br>
In this case this is the first Sky raid I have led. Our guild can sport an average raid of roughly 53rd level. On this particular night, we got lucky, and added 2 60th levels to our ranks. <br>
<br>
It's not easy running the raid the first time. It's not really easy when mistakes are made that have to be cleaned up using the most precious resource we had (time).<br>
<br>
Several hours were lost trying to get forward motion regained. We wound up with problems, and difficulties that probably would not happen with a raid group who was more familiar with the plane.<br>
<br>
But it did. I am a huge advocate of not wasting something (liek dragons dying to a server reset), but if you stuff 60 people in the same zone and have all of them casting, fighting and jumping about, you will wind up with problems. <br>
<br>
It's bad enough when a guild goes after Vox, Nagafen, or Trak and you have the normal hunting parties in those dungeons, but to have 2 complete raids on the same zone? You are asking for problems. <br>
<br>
I believe this is true for Sky, Hate, and any other zone which (by MoB population) can sustain 2 complete raids, the zone just can't do it (particularly the pre-RoK zones).<br>
<br>
I must admit I was somewhat disappointed in that rather than asking how far we had made it, the assumption was made that we did not know some hidden rule about raiding Sky.<br>
<br>
I have been on several Sky raids, and each one hunted Isle 1 on their first port up night to gain keys, and usually camping, though occasionally they take Dojorn. <br>
<br>
The second night is ALSO a portup night, so Isle 1 is rehunted for keys, and the riad meets up either on Isle 1 or Dojorn's and moves from there.<br>
<br>
Tonight I was told I was wrong, and apparently so are the raid leaders from many of the other fine guilds on Brell. It kind of boggles the mind that so many people did not know about this Isle 1-4 in a night rule.<br>
<br>
Honestly, I opted for Thursday - Saturday HOPING another guild would take Sunday and Monday so that the plane WOULD get the most out of the long US holiday.<br>
<br>
Pardon what may sound like ranting, but this comes after a long drawn out series of problems that has plagued this raid, and it's now almost 3am here, and I am looking forward to logging in and having to find a few enchanters to help me finish as far as we can.  <p><img src="http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/224/17/32241726.jpg"><BR><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=1323">Valeer Shadowsbaine Reaver of the 52nd Season</A> <br>
<ahref="http://theca.n3.net/">The Combine Alliance</a></br>
<br>Alea iacta est. </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualannia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alannia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Talaena's Tang</span><br>  Posts: 880<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/26/01 12:02:57 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://images.andale.com/f2/112/123/6102561/990039556545_alien.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sky rule need to be changed with strong guide line</span><hr size=1> I too am for optimal utilization of the plane of Sky.  It was not our intention to step on anyones toes, and to be quite frank, our plan was to be CAMPED on isle 4 or higher about 3 hours ago.  We were wiped out on isle 3.  Did we do it on purpose?  No, I should say not!!  Who likes an expensive corpse recovery?<br>
<br>
There are several reasons why we were not on island 4 when you logged in Roatus.  One of those reasons was a group of folks sending tells to our raid leader arguing with him for a half an hour with him indicating that they had every intention of coming up and clearing as far as they could tomorrow...during our scheduled raid time.<br>
<br>
I do not take your post as a rant against CA.  But I will say that what you are suggesting makes it difficult for any guild to LEARN the plane, the way the higher level guilds have done before us.  One day, we and other guilds will be able to clear Sky the way you outline it to be.  Today, we proved we can't.  <br>
<br>
We don't want anything wasted any more than you do.  And we fully well intend on jumping down tomorrow when our raid reservation time has ended, regardless of what island we get to.  We are thrilled for the chance to try what others before us have succeeded in doing.<br>
<br>
Perhaps, had we been gifted with the ability to see into the future, and know what would happen, we would not have reserved these days.  I can't do that though, can you?  Hours and hours and hours of planning went into this raid.  We've almost exhausted our guild raid fun putting this raid on, and dealing with the CR that we did not expect.  Our team was psyched for success.  30 people appear impressed enough with this effort that they are willing to stick with us tomorrow (again, our scheduled day) to recover our separated companions, and continue on as we planned to do, despite mistakes made and unforseen issues arrisen.  Despite a VERY long corpse recovery, involving the reporting up of the entire raid party, Morale seems pretty high.<br>
<br>
If the rules are changed, we will, of course, abide by them.  But the 24th, 25th and 26 are our scheduled days to be in the plane.  NOT to take away from the rest of the server.  But to do something that The Combine Alliance fully believes it can do, and has never done before.<br>
<br>
I hope the older raiders can understand how proud that makes us feel.  It was very disheartening to watch Sundays raiders inform our raid leader that they were coming up Saturday...on our day.<br>
<br>
This is also not a rant, but as it is a discussion, I can only offer my opinion of your suggestion from a personal standpoint.  I cannot believe that there are not other guilds out there that would feel the same way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uroatusbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoatusBH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/26/01 1:38:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sky rule need to be changed with strong guide line</span><hr size=1> Any kind or practice/learning is needed. I know that, i did that.<br>
What i want to say is, 3 days reservation is not for practice.<br>
And most of ppl don't know that.<br>
That's why i think we need to mention it on board.<br>
<br>
This time you reserved 1st day only for 1st isle camp<br>
where mobs are 4hours spawn and keys are sold by vendor.<br>
If you knew more about this plane you wouldn't do this.<br>
Why did you reserve full 3days?<br>
Because other guild(ex Abyss) are reserving 3days. And it is allowed to reserve 3 days by rule.<br>
You saw it and tried to do same.<br>
But abyss can do upto 7th isle, you were new to sky.<br>
This difference is the problem.<br>
Whether intentional or not, what you did is, same as reserving PoF triple days straight.<br>
You stayed up on 1st isle those 3days and 2-7th isles were wasted whole this weekend.<br>
3days reservation is for &quot;different isle&quot; raids on each days.<br>
<br>
You didn't know, and you made mistake this time.<br>
Many ppl don't know, and they will make mistake in future as you did.<br>
So, let's inform ppl so that they can know before they raid.<br>
This is what i am talking in this post.<br>
<br>
I lived in Brell long time, i have been to sky since this zone was added in game.<br>
Saw many failures. Everyone(include myself) died and failed SAME way.<br>
<br>
If raiders are new to sky, i am sure they will fail 99% because sky is very tricky.<br>
If they are new to sky, i am sure they will stuck on 1-2 isles first time.<br>
<br>
If ppl are new to sky, let them try only one day first time.<br>
If they fail, let them reserve another day and retry.<br>
If they succeed, let them reserve 2days for higher isle for more challange.<br>
This is ideal reservation form of multiple days.<br>
<br>
I will edit Sky reservation rule and will post here.<br>
And you can compare the difference.<br>
<br>
PS.<br>
I am not complaining about the delay you made.<br>
Since CA reserved sky first and i try to make my raid during it,<br>
i was ready for such trouble.<br>
<br>
Roatus <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uroatusbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoatusBH</A> at: 5/26/01 1:46:14 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uroatusbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoatusBH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/26/01 2:30:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   my idea of new rule</span><hr size=1> Go and read sky reservation rule.<br>
Mostly there is no problem except one part.<br>
<br>
&gt;A sky raid may claim between one and three consecutive days in the plane. <br>
<br>
This &quot;rough&quot; limitation is causing the problem.<br>
Because this can be monopolization of zone for full 3 days.<br>
Here is my suggestion for solution.<br>
<br>
Make rule #1 like...<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
I. You cannot post more then 2 weeks ahead of the start of the first day of the raid. You can post max 3 reservations for different isles.One reservation post for one day. Any post will be deleted if it breaks any portion of this rule. Board time will be used to determine this. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Now, sky reservation post is like...<br>
[Guild X, sky raid 20th - 22th]<br>
<br>
instead of that, make it like<br>
[Guild X, sky 1-4th isle 20th]<br>
[Guild X, sky 5-6th isle 21th]<br>
[Guild X, sky 7-8th isle 22th]<br>
<br>
Look at old reservation style.<br>
This allows them to keep full isles for full 3 days.<br>
<br>
Look at my idea.<br>
If raiders clarify which isle they will go,<br>
we can make other days for free.<br>
In this example, 1-4th isle should be free on 21th.<br>
So other ppl can reserve this date.<br>
With old method, ppl can't know 1-4th is free on 21th or not.<br>
They need to wait until 23th. This is waste. <br>
In case Guild X fails to do 1-4th on 20th, they just need to give up 21th and 22th<br>
because they simply don't have power to do higher isle and can't go.<br>
Reserving undoable place is non sense.<br>
<br>
If ppl are not sure if they can make it,<br>
and want to learn/practice, just reserve one day for trial.<br>
<br>
I want official comment about this reserving method, from Chants and Adun.<br>
And want any opinions if there is bad point with my idea.<br>
<br>
Roatus <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uroatusbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoatusBH</A> at: 5/26/01 3:36:44 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvumil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vumil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Administrator <img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle><br><font color=#A0B0E0>&lt;<a href=http://www.silentredemption.org>Silent Redemption</a>&gt;  </font></span><br>  Posts: 1263<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/26/01 4:36:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my idea of new rule</span><hr size=1> Thats a good idea Roatus.. and it should make the zone more utilized. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uflatlands3.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flatlands3</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/26/01 6:23:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my idea of new rule</span><hr size=1> I am a lucky guest of the CA sky raid team and I again echo the thought that *no one* had the intention of still being on the first isle today.  I think that this raid is being extremely well run with raid leaders carefully explaining over and over to the numerous &quot;sky newbies&quot; how to preform on this raid.  The raiders are also being patient and not flaming the leaders for not being able to progress further.  The group leaders are also preforming their roles extremely well - keeping groups informed of discussions happening in chat.  <br>
<br>
As with life, sometimes the unexpected does happen.  I would say that the delay is **not** the fault of the raid leaders.  Nor would I say this group is not competent to hunt this zone.  All the people on this raid are gaining valuable experience in a new enviroment.  As far as I can see there has been no wasted down time where the leaders have been sitting doing nothing.  There is also no farming of loot on the first isle.   At 230am est they were still planning to get the 3rd isle cleared and camp on the 4th.  However, some of us have RL committment that require some sleep.  At this point they made - what I feel ws the wise decision - to call it a night and start the ball rolling again today.  I say *cheer* to the raid leaders for keeping a nasty CR going as smoothly as possible. <p><font size=2><font color=Tan ><b>TheGrouping Druid!</b><br>
