</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwayun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wayun</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_whitespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>aka Valeer</span><br>  Posts: 585<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/26/01 6:31:51 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/image/49/2586249.jpg?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my idea of new rule</span><hr size=1> So I gues, when do we get to reserve Sky for 3 days?<br>
<br>
Do we get a special Card (Guys!!! Just one more punch and we can reserve Sky!!!), or will some of you give us new raid leaders a test, and we get our official &quot;Brell Raider's License&quot;?<br>
<br>
I guess I don't get it. I really don't. You are saying &quot;You can't reserve a plane unless you can prove you can pull the raid off.&quot; That sounds like the most increadable case of 60th level arrogance I have ever heard. This may come as a shock to you, but not all guilds are populated with 60th level characters, and not all of us are carrying our epic weapons and are replacing Knuark armor with Skyshrine armor. We don't all hunt Temple of Veeshan for a good time...<br>
<br>
Now I understand that for some of you, you can set a time table on Sky. &quot;Isle 1 = 20 minutes, Isle 2 = 1 hour 15 mins&quot;, but we can't, and if you were honest with yourselves you'd know you couldn't either when you were raiding in groups averaging 52nd level.<br>
<br>
The plain sits empty on weeknights. Nights that a damn good team can take easy. Weeknights are hard nights to raid, peeps have work the next morning, so a tighter schedual is required. The weekends are easier raids, lots of people can comfortably raid on the weekend. All I see here is someone who does not have Rants anymore who is upset that a newbie took a holiday weekend to raid. <br>
<br>
I see posts about restricting who can do what and where, and how it's pointless to reserve, and how we should just FFA / FCFS the planes, etc. If we do, do you REALLY think this is going to get any better? Do you REALLY think that if Sky was FCFS that the raiders up there would care one way or another about your time table? <br>
<br>
What about post SoL, when (and you know it will happen) better armor and weapons make Sky even easier, and a tight raid crew all 60+ and maxxed out on the new &quot;Post 60 development&quot; can clear Sky in 2 days. Are you going to impose a new timetable then, making it even harder to learn? <br>
<br>
